         <abstract>
            <p>Although the domestic flat glass industry is currently enjoying a banner year, a 60 per cent increase in capacity is anticipated over the next four years, raising in some investors' minds the possibility of over-capacity and concomitant price deterioration. In the author's opinion, the danger has been exaggerated. Although margins on float glass are likely to narrow, the long term profitability of the industry should improve as the less profitable and more labor intensive plate and sheet glass facilities are replaced; sheet and plate glass capacity are declining even as float glass captures a larger share of the total flat glass market.</p>
